  <exercise label="ex_2_7">
    <statement>
      <p>The formula for computing the final amount if one is earning
                        compound interest is given on Wikipedia as</p>
      <image source="SimplePythonData/Figures/compoundInterest.png" width="50%" alt="formula for compound interest"/>
      <p>Write a Python program that assigns the principal amount of 10000 to
                        variable P, assign to n the value 12, and assign to r the interest
                        rate of 8% (0.08).  Then have the program prompt the user for the number of years,
                        t, that the money will be compounded for.  Calculate and print the final
                        amount after t years.</p>
    </statement>
    <program interactive="activecode" language="python" xml:id="ex_2_7_editor">
      <input>

        </input>
    </program>
    <solution>
      <program xml:id="spd_q7_answer" language="python">
        <input>
## question 7 solution ##

P = 10000
n = 12
r = 0.08

t = int(input("Compound for how many years? "))

final = P * ( ((1 + (r/n)) ** (n * t)) )

print ("The final amount after", t, "years is", final)
        </input>
      </program>
    </solution>
